			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=136614#p136614"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=51" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">Nadia</a></strong> &raquo; Nov 28th, '07, 07:06 </p>

			

			<div class="content"><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/2007/nov/27/bbc.digitalvideo">http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/20 ... gitalvideo</a><!-- m -->
<br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>the BBC's iPlayer DRM prevents you from watching a show more than 28 days after you downloaded it. <br /><br />By contrast, shows that you record on your VCR or PC can be watched forever.</div></blockquote></div>

